Mr. HARDESTY presented a proposition from Messrs. Henry C. Painter
                                   and William M. Merwin to discharge the duties of the postoffice
                                   for the General Assembly, as follows:

Mr. O'BRIEN fully concurred in the opinion that the
                                   resolution should be passed, and not a substitute for it;
                                   therefore, he favored the motion to refer.

